# apt packages spud-router depends on. One per line; blank lines and #comments
# ignored. Single source of truth for both install.sh (fresh install) and
# update.py (OTA provisioning), so a feature whose package landed in a newer
# release gets installed on the next update instead of needing install.sh.
# `apt-get install -y` on an already-present package is a no-op, so re-running
# this on every update is safe and idempotent.
